Zimbabwe Earns $174 Million From Marange Diamonds, Herald Says

-- B y   N e l s o n   G o r e   B a n y a
-- 
2011-02-15T07:46:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/zimbabwe-earns-174-million-from-marange-diamonds-herald-says.html
  Zimbabwe  earned $174 million from
diamond sales from the Marange diamond field this year, the
Herald reported, citing a state mining official.  The money is from sales by Mbada Mining Ltd. and Marange
Resources Ltd., the Harare-based, state-owned newspaper cited
the official as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nelson Gore Banya in Johannesburg at 
 ngbanya@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  